 die durch den Ruhm des Autors letztlich nur unvollständig überschrieben worden sind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aItalian literatureyTo 1400xHistory and criticism. 0aVoice in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 4aDante. 4aGeschlechterforschung. 4aPetrarca. 4aStimme. 4aTrecento. 4aVoice. 4agender. 70(DE-601)1044846830(DE-588)4273141-0aSprechengMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1046536040(DE-588)4113617-2aFraugMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1050084510(DE-588)4221636-9aStimmegMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)3264043410(DE-588)4616685-3aSubjektgPhilosophie, Motiv2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104282300 cprintz978311043771340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110428162423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110428162.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DKUb2016